<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-01-14T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-01-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">368.117/44: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-14T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                        1920—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Your 861, November 18, 6 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Endeavor ascertain whether similar treatment will be accorded naturalized
                            American citizens who complied with American law but were exempted or
                            given deferred classification; also what treatment will be accorded
                            those who have neither served nor registered for service because not
                            within military age, absent from country or other satisfactory reason,
                            especially in view pending naturalization Convention.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
